From eec8bb85a0c364bb0f597c836111f7714c879fe6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Xi Ruoyao <xry111@xry111.site>
Date: Wed, 12 Nov 2025 18:21:01 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 348/348] AOSCOS: Revert "PCI: Extend isolated function probing
 to LoongArch"

This reverts commit a02fd05661d73a8507dd70dd820e9b984490c545.

It's said to be related with some error report from pata_legacy.  Maybe
we should just disable pata_legacy on LoongArch (or even anything other
than x86).
---
 include/linux/hypervisor.h | 3 ---
 1 file changed, 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/include/linux/hypervisor.h b/include/linux/hypervisor.h
index be5417303ecf..9efbc54e35e5 100644
--- a/include/linux/hypervisor.h
+++ b/include/linux/hypervisor.h
@@ -37,9 +37,6 @@ static inline bool hypervisor_isolated_pci_functions(void)
 	if (IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_S390))
 		return true;
 
-	if (IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_LOONGARCH))
-		return true;
-
 	return jailhouse_paravirt();
 }
 
